<item>
            <title>[DERBY-5504] SecureServerTest, Driver40UnbootedTest and replication tests not prepared for space in java.home</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-5504</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;SecureServerTest, Driver40UnbootedTest and the replication tests fork JVMs by calling Runtime.exec() methods that take the command as a String parameter, not a String[]. This causes problems like the ones seen in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-5490&quot; title=&quot;Lots of error trying to spawn a JVM in the SecureServerTest and Replication tests when running on the preview JDK 7 on Mac OS X&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-5490&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-5490&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; when there&apos;s a space in $&lt;/p&gt;
{java.home}
&lt;p&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The tests should be rewritten to use the helper method BaseTestCase.execJavaCmd(), which handles this case correctly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12531611">DERBY-5504</key>
            <summary>SecureServerTest, Driver40UnbootedTest and replication tests not prepared for space in java.home</summary>
